Bolstered the server-side protocol modules in ssmtp.rs and spop3.rs so they now behave like real protocol engines instead of empty placeholders.

What is in there now:

ssmtp.rs: banner, EHLO/HELO, STARTTLS, AUTH LOGIN challenge flow, MAIL FROM, RCPT TO, DATA, NOOP, RSET, QUIT, typed reply object, basic message capture, and line-by-line command handling.
spop3.rs: greeting, USER, PASS, STAT, LIST, RETR, TOP, DELE, NOOP, QUIT, typed reply object, in-memory mailbox/message model, and command parsing/response generation.
mod.rs already exports them beside the client modules as requested.
I ran cargo fmt and timeout 25 make run. Build finished cleanly with no compile errors observed.

